# Normalize all text files to LF in the repo and on checkout on every
# platform. Prevents CRLF drift when Windows editors (or Git-for-Windows
# with core.autocrlf=true) write working-tree files as CRLF, which then
# show up as phantom "modified" entries to Linux-side tooling (including
# the FUSE-mounted sandbox this repo is edited from).
#
# text=auto lets git auto-detect binary files and leave them untouched.
# eol=lf forces LF in the working tree for every file classified as text.
* text=auto eol=lf
